Juche Idea Study Group Formed in Russia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- The Tynda City Group for the Study of the Juche Idea was formed in Tynda City, Amur Region, Russia, on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's start of work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea on May 31.
 G. F. Astakhov, special correspondent of the newspaper Amurskaya Pravda in Tynda, in a report made at the inaugural ceremony said that the group would deeply study the Juche idea which was founded by President Kim Il Sung and is being developed and enriched by Kim Jong Il, widely introduce it to broad strata of Russians and conduct positive activities for boosting the friendship between Russia and the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Astakhov was elected chairman of the group at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the ceremony.

Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works Published 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- The Workers' Party of Korea Publishing House brought out "Complete Collection of Kim Il Sung's Works" Vol. 54, a library of the immortal Juche idea which comprehensively and systematically deals with his famous works in a chronological order.
 The book contains 24 works including speeches, talks and concluding speeches made by President Kim Il Sung from March to June, Juche 63 (1974), the historical period in which the Korean revolution reached a new stage of its development under the banner of modeling the whole society on the Juche idea and the entire party and state and all the people were out in the vigorous drive to build socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President in his works including "On Effectively Conducting the Work with People and Strengthening the Party Guidance to the Administrative and Economic Work" clarified the principled matters arising in further strengthening the WPK and decisively increasing its leadership role. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Laid down in his works including "On Effecting New Surge in Socialist Economic Construction" are a policy for attaining new goals in the socialist economic construction and militant tasks and ways to implement it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The works also underscore the importance of the work to remould man in accomplishing the cause of modeling the whole society on the Juche idea, the issue of revolutionizing and working-classizing the Party members and other working people and the policies and ways to energetically push ahead with the work to revolutionize Pyongyang City and thus transform all other parts of the country on a revolutionary pattern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President in the works including "Answers to Questions Raised by the Chief Editor of Al Sahafa, Organ of the Sudanese Government" and "Talk to the President of the Republic of Senegal" clarified the important issues facing the progressive people of the world in victoriously advancing the national liberation movement and the building of a new society under the banner of the anti-imperialist struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The book also deals with the issue of totally abolishing the tax system in the DPRK, the issue of letting the entire army and all the people learn from war experience and earnestly study military affairs, the issue of forcing the U.S. troops to withdraw from south Korea and achieving the reunification of the country and the issue of adopting a peace agreement between the DPRK and the U.S., etc.

Reunification Festival Announced in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- An announcement ceremony of a festival of Inchon citizens for reunification was reportedly held at an open-air theatre of the Inchon House of Culture and Art on June 5 under the sponsorship of the Inchon Regional Committee for the Promotion of  Our National Meeting for Commemorating the Fourth Anniversary of the June 15 Joint Declaration.
 Exhibited around the theatre were photos showing south-north civilian exchange activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  At the ceremony Co-chairman of the committee O Yong Ho and other speakers said that many citizens should participate in the meeting so as to achieve reunification, the desire of fellow countrymen, at an early date. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization set a period of the festival from June 5 to 17 and named the street before the house the reunification street and the house plaza the plaza of great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ceremony was followed by an art performance.

Second Anti-U.S. Sit-down in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- The People for Achieving Peace and Reunification reportedly staged in front of the building of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade on June 5 the second sit-down in the "Period of the intensive struggle regarding the ninth round of the Future of south Korea-U.S. alliance (FOTA) policy initiative talks and negotiations on the reduction of U.S. troops in south Korea".
 Protesters conducted information activities exposing the bellicose nature of the U.S. imperialists' new military strategy, shouting slogans "death-defying opposition to the U.S. moves to turn its troops in south Korea into Northeast Asian regional troops threatening peace in the Korean peninsula", "Reduce the U.S. troops in south Korea without combat power buildup" and so on. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said they can never tolerate the intention of the U.S. to turn the south Korea-U.S. "alliance" into a "regional alliance" as it is a scheme to make the Korean peninsula its forward base for keeping its hegemony in Northeast Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They warned that if the authorities permit the conversion of the U.S. troops stationed in south Korea into Northeast Asian regional troops in the interests of the U.S. and accept the plan for the combat power buildup of the U.S. troops, they would face the resistance of all the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the Family Movement for Realizing Democracy and labor organizations and many citizens went to the scene of the strike to encourage protesters.

June 15 March Group of Youth Inaugurated in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- The South Korean Council of Youth Organizations reportedly held an inaugural ceremony of the  June 15 march group of youth for withdrawal of the decision on the troop dispatch to Iraq and implementation of the joint declaration in Seoul on June 5.
 At the ceremony Chairman of the council Jon Sang Bong hoped that the march group would be a pioneer in achieving independence, reunification and great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Head of the march group Pak Hui Jin, chairman of the Committee for National Reunification of the council, said that it is natural for the youth to stand in the van of the struggle for implementation of the joint declaration and national reunification and that he would actively strive to ensure pilgrimage activities successfully. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Members of the march group shouted slogans "let's take the lead in implementing the joint declaration" and so on. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ceremony was followed by an art performance.

Marathon Race for Reunification in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- The second marathon race for reunification was reportedly held at the River Han Citizens' Park in Youido, Seoul, on June 5 to mark the 4th anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration.
 Participating in the race were more than 600 teachers, students and trade union members in Seoul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mun Kyong Sik, chairman of the south Korean Federation of Peasants Associations who is co-chairman of the organizing committee of the race, said in his speech the June 15 joint declaration is a promise of the 70 million fellow countrymen to achieve national reunification by the concerted efforts of the Korean nation, the master of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The marathon race will be compost for reunification which will help toward thoroughly implementing the June 15 joint declaration, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the race began. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the race the participants conducted diverse propaganda activities, flying over 100 kites bearing the desire for reunification.

